<%= content_for :title, 'HTML vs XHTML' %>
<article id="html-xhtml">
  <p>
    <strong>XHTML</strong> is an <strong>XML</strong> serialized version of <strong>HTML</strong>
  </p>
  <p>Buhhh?</p>
  <p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th></th>
          <th>HTML5</th>
          <th>XHTML5</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>MIME Type</td>
          <td><code>text/html</code></td>
          <td><code>application/xhtml+xml</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>noscript</code></td>
          <td>Yes</td>
          <td>No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Attributes</td>
          <td><code>disabled</code></td>
          <td><code>disabled="disabled"</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Case</td>
          <td>UPPER Or lower</td>
          <td>all lowercase</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Self closing tags</td>
          <td>No</td>
          <td>Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>All tags must be closed</td>
          <td>No</td>
          <td>Yes</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </p>
  <p>
    Source: <a href="http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec/Overview.html#html-vs-xhtml">
      http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec/Overview.html#html-vs-xhtml</a>
  </p>
